.TH pif-registry-remove 1  "pif-registry-remove " 
.SH NAME
pif\-registry\-remove \- Remove a registry entry by extension name
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpif\-registry\-remove\fR [\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-\-path\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fINAME\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Remove a registry entry by extension name
.PP
Deletes the record from the pif registry without touching the files on disk. Use this to tell pif to forget an installation (e.g. before reinstalling to a different path).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-path\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Restrict removal to a specific install path (optional)

When an extension has been installed to multiple paths, this narrows the removal to the matching entry only.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fINAME\fR>
Name of the extension to remove from the registry
